{"type":"message","id":"b608c8aa","parentId":"9e2cc6cb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:29:04.364Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b4595y8h7py7_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 151843\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most concrete next step is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment - implementing the classifier on pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The experiment needs to:\r\n1. Analyze pulse log files\r\n2. Classify content as invariant vs variant\r\n3. Predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that I can work with. The recent pulse log mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-23 150841.md`. I should check if there are other pulse logs in `logs/` directory.\r\n\r\nSince I need to advance Phase 1 and test the TIC hypothesis, I should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs\r\n2. Create a simple TIC classifier script or analysis\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction and that I need to implement the TIC classifier, I should create a script that:\r\n- Reads pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (structural elements that repeat)\r\n- Identifies variant patterns (content that changes)\r\n- Tests prediction capability\r\n\r\nLet me first check what pulse logs exist, then create a TIC experiment script.\r\n\r\nActually, I should create the TIC experiment script as a PowerShell file that can analyze the pulse logs. This directly implements the \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" from the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me craft a response that:\r\n1. Observes the current state (ready to implement TIC experiment)\r\n2. Takes action: create a PowerShell TIC classifier script\r\n3. Provides the mutation in the required format\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 advancement requires testing the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis via the TIC experiment. The pulse logs exist but no classifier is yet implemented to test invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that analyzes pulse logs for invariant structure (header patterns, metadata, formatting) vs variant content (ideas, insights, findings). This implements the experiment outlined in `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$logDir = \"logs\"\r\n$outputDir = \"tic/results\"\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Collect pulse logs\r\n$logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $logDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Extract invariant markers (structural patterns)\r\n$invariantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"### [A-Z]\",           # Section headers\r\n    \"^### OBSERVATION\",    # Required sections\r\n    \"^### ACTION\",\r\n    \"^### MUTATION\",\r\n    \"^\\`\\`\\`\",              # Code blocks\r\n    \"^file:\",              # File references\r\n    \"^\\-\\s\\[\",             # Checkbox items\r\n    \"^## \"                 # Headers\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Phase 3: Extract variant content (idea-bearing text)\r\n$variantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"^[A-Z].*\\.$\",         # Sentences\r\n    \"^\\- \",                # List items with content\r\n    \"^[A-Z][a-z]+:\"        # Labeled values\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Phase 4: Classification + Output\r\n@{\r\n    Logs = $logs.Count\r\n    InvariantPatterns = $invariantPatterns.Count\r\n    VariantPatterns = $variantPatterns.Count\r\n    Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n} | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File \"$outputDir/classification_$(Get-Date -Format 'yyyyMMdd_HHmmss').json\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Classification Complete - $($logs.Count) logs processed\"\r\nfile: tic/classifier.ps1\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 15:18:59\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774294144361}}
